display="inline"><![CDATA[\sigma ]]></fr:tex> to <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f(x)]]></fr:tex>).</fr:p><fr:p>Then the number of extensions of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\sigma ]]></fr:tex> to an isomorphism <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\Bbbk \to \Bbbk ']]></fr:tex> is at most <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[[\Bbbk  : \mathbb {F}]]]></fr:tex>. If <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f(x)]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link
type="local"
href="nt-0025.xml"
addr="nt-0025"
title="Separable Polynomial">separable</fr:link>, then it is exactly <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[[\Bbbk  : \mathbb {F}]]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
 
   
